    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\n`help vim.lsp.client` has a portion about `server_capabilities` which needs to be more descriptive. All you take away from the current description is that it's a table that's sent by the server. But it should ideally also describe what values the table has, such as `documentFormattingProvider` and `renameProvider`.\r\n\r\nSo either have  (1) a dedicated page to all the available options or (2) a link to whichever place provides and maintains all the information about it, i.e. [lsp server protocol specifications](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/)\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nInformation on `{server_capabilities}` should be explicitly stated with either a dedicated section or a redirect to whichever place has it.\r\n\r\nI don't mind creating a PR with some additions if it's necessary. ",
